&lt;p&gt;The&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Jewish Cultural Employee Resource Group&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;invites you to join us on&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;October 7th &lt;/strong&gt;from&lt;strong&gt; 11:30am &lt;/strong&gt;to&lt;strong&gt; 1:30pm &lt;/strong&gt;at &lt;strong&gt;Hammer 301&lt;/strong&gt; to commemorate one year since the events of October 7th. We will remember lives lost, pray for those in captivity, honor the survivors and heroes, and unite in our communical resilience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Programming will include hearing the story of survivor &lt;strong&gt;Elinor Bitton&lt;/strong&gt; from Kfar Aza and&amp;nbsp;memorial songs and psalms presented by &lt;strong&gt;Cantors David Farhi&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;and &lt;strong&gt;Zevi Muller&lt;/strong&gt;. This event is brought to you by&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Chabad CUIMC&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;and the&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Faces of October Seventh&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;in partnership with the&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Jewish Cultural ERG&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This event is open to all Columbia University and NewYork-Presbyterian students, employees, and faculty.&lt;/p&gt;
