&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;The Society of Fellows hosts the Thursday Lecture Series (TLS), which runs regularly throughout the academic year. The Fall Semester TLS, our Fellows present their own work, chaired by Columbia faculty.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;God, Fatherland, Family: Integralismo and the Making of the Far-Right in Twentieth Century Brazil&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Lecture by&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href="https://sofheyman.org/persons/daniela-moraes-traldi"&gt;Daniela Moraes Traldi&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
Chaired by&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href="https://sofheyman.org/persons/benjamin-steege"&gt;Benjamin Steege&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this talk, Daniela Moraes Traldi examines how&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;Integralistas&lt;/em&gt;, the Brazilian fascists who purportedly numbered one million members by 1935, created Brazil&amp;rsquo;s first-ever mass political organization and how they survived after the mid-1940s pushed for by women. In the 1930s,&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;Integralistas&lt;/em&gt;&amp;nbsp;envisioned creating what they called a Christian holistic state (&lt;em&gt;Estado Integral&lt;/em&gt;), in which corporatism, nationalism, and faith would sustain the country&amp;rsquo;s very existence in opposition to communism, materialism, and liberalism.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Offering a fresh analytical framework to this history, Traldi argues that&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;Integralistas&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;were able to meaningfully re-group after the Era of Fascism, and that women emerged as key socio-political agents for the &amp;ldquo;reinvention&amp;rdquo; of Brazilian Integralismo from Latin America&amp;rsquo;s largest fascist movement of the 1930s to an influential far-right Christian nationalist group after the mid-1940s. Drawing from largely unexplored sources, such as correspondence, iconographic material, private collections, and oral histories, and building from important scholarship of Latin America, Traldi shows how gender, fascism, and religion appeared as intertwined, complex categories of analysis especially during the Cold War in Latin America. Also, her talk raises an alarm in the present: the&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;Integralista&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;recipe of God, Fatherland, Family lasted much longer than previously thought.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Register &lt;a href="https://www.eventbrite.com/e/god-fatherland-family-integralismo-and-the-far-right-in-brazil-tickets-1001456903557?aff=oddtdtcreator" target="_blank"&gt;HERE&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Join us to an exclusive evening of intellectual and cultural exploration on Thursday, October 10, at 7:30pm in MASA&amp;rsquo;s stunning terrace view to the Basilica Santa Maria Maggiore.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The evening will feature an engaging presentation by Richard Begam, Professor of English at the University of Wisconsin-Madison. Known for his expertise in modernist literature and postcolonial studies, Richard will share his deep insights into La Grande Bellezza, the Oscar-winning film by Paolo Sorrentino, exploring its themes of beauty, decadence, and the search for meaning in contemporary society.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;About the Speaker:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Richard Begam is the author of several influential works, including Samuel Beckett and the End of Modernity and Modernism, Postcolonialism, and Globalism. His research spans an impressive range of topics, from 20th-century British and Irish literature to the intersection of philosophy and modernism. His talk on La Grande Bellezza will offer a unique perspective on this cinematic masterpiece. Learn more about&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href="https://english.wisc.edu/staff/begam-richard/"&gt;Richard Begam here&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Venue and Program:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The MASA Terrace provides a beautiful setting for the evening, with panoramic views of the historic Basilica Santa Maria Maggiore, offering the perfect backdrop for our gathering.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We will begin with a welcoming glass of sparkling wine and light networking on the terrace as we await the arrival of alumni and friends.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Following this, we will move to the conference room, where Professor Begam will share his insights during a captivating presentation with pictures and video.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The evening will conclude back on the rooftop with networking cocktails and a selection of delicious appetizers, celebrating the rich flavors of Italy.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please confirm your attendance&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;by October 7, 10:00am&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;by making your payment, 35 euro per person&lt;/strong&gt;.&amp;nbsp;Space is limited to twenty people, please reserve your spot early for this inspiring evening of fine conversation, stunning views, and culinary delight.&lt;/p&gt;

