&lt;p&gt;Are you curious how you might leverage AI in your teaching and course design? Have you been considering the role AI might play in your course assignments and activities? Looking to learn more about the impact and benefits on using AI as a partner to human thinking?&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Then join the CTL for a discussion of &lt;a href="https://www.aacu.org/people/jos%C3%A9-antonio-bowen"&gt;Jos&amp;eacute; Antonio Bowen&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href="https://www.aacu.org/people/c-edward-watson"&gt;C. Edward Watson&lt;/a&gt;&amp;rsquo;s new book &lt;em&gt;Teaching with AI: A Practical Guide to a New Era of Human Learning&lt;/em&gt;, where we will discuss these questions and more! You will join colleagues across three 60-minute sessions organized around the book&amp;rsquo;s thematic framing: thinking with AI, teaching with AI, and learning with AI. In addition to discussing the book itself, you will have an opportunity to experiment with some of the ideas proposed in the book, as well as discuss your own course materials in relation to AI.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
