&lt;p&gt;Now in its 11th year, the annual &lt;a href="https://nam02.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.weinberg.cuimc.columbia.edu%2Feducation%2Flindenauer-lecture&amp;amp;data=05%7C01%7Chm2784%40cumc.columbia.edu%7C9ebffa3fb206459ec3ac08dba4bf9e8d%7Cb0002a9b0017404d97dc3d3bab09be81%7C0%7C0%7C638284915125852778%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&amp;amp;sdata=Ek%2FbHGtHhw3KpWZ1SwTYQmYawsXLDAsxyWeXx8SoEh4%3D&amp;amp;reserved=0"&gt;Lindenauer Lecture&lt;/a&gt; invites leading cerebral palsy experts around the world&amp;nbsp;to discuss groundbreaking new ideas and emerging technologies related to the care of cerebral palsy patients.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
