&lt;p&gt;The 2024 presidential election is guaranteed to be one of the most consequential in modern history. This forum will explore not only the politics of this cycle but also the ways in which those politics &amp;mdash; and the politicians &amp;mdash; were framed, reported on and examined in our media coverage. This conversation is meant to be candid, self-critical and a starting place to begin thinking about the administration that will take office in 2025 and what this election means for the United States and the world.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This program is cosponsored by the &lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href="https://igp.sipa.columbia.edu/"&gt;SIPA&amp;#39;s Institute of Global Politics&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; and &lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href="https://journalism.columbia.edu/"&gt;Columbia Journalism School&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Program Participants:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
