&lt;h2&gt;Fostering AI Literacy in the Classroom (For Faculty)&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A 75-minute discussion-based workshop for Columbia Faculty.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Before leveraging AI tools for your teaching and learning needs, it&amp;rsquo;s important to first think about AI literacy: what is it? How might you advance your own and your students&amp;rsquo;? What are the elements of AI literacy that make sense for your course context?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this 75-minute session, you will be introduced to an &lt;a href="https://er.educause.edu/articles/2024/6/a-framework-for-ai-literacy" target="_blank"&gt;AI literacy framework&lt;/a&gt; that emphasizes understanding of AI, its use and application, and analysis and evaluation of AI as a tool. Join in conversation with your colleagues around why it&amp;rsquo;s important to foster students&amp;rsquo; AI literacy, and how you might do that within the context of your course and discipline. To get the most out of this session and learn about varying approaches to AI literacy across campus, participants will be expected to share their thoughts and experiences throughout this discussion-based session.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
