&lt;h2&gt;Designing Poll Questions That Go Beyond Recall (For Faculty)&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A 60-minute workshop for Columbia Faculty.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Want to use polls to get students to engage more deeply with course concepts during class?&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this workshop, faculty will learn the first steps to developing poll questions that encourage students to move beyond recalling information and engage in higher order cognitive processes, such as applying concepts or evaluating hypotheses. Faculty can incorporate these poll questions into their classes to engage, assess, and guide their students in real time. This workshop combines the cognitive framework Bloom&amp;rsquo;s Taxonomy and the audience response system &lt;a href="https://ctl.columbia.edu/ars/"&gt;Poll Everywhere&lt;/a&gt;, which Columbia faculty and students can access. Come ready with one course concept and a few associated questions to work on during this workshop. We will also briefly explore generative AI prompts you can use to draft poll questions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;**For this workshop, faculty are expected to have some familiarity with Poll Everywhere. For faculty new to Poll Everywhere, you are encouraged to attend the &lt;a href="https://events.columbia.edu/cal/event/eventView.do?b=de&amp;amp;calPath=%2Fpublic%2Fcals%2FMainCal&amp;amp;guid=CAL-00bbdb71-83f996ef-0183-fc23a146-0000474devents@columbia.edu&amp;amp;recurrenceId="&gt;Engaging Students with Poll Everywhere&lt;/a&gt; demo preceding this workshop and / or review this short video &lt;a href="https://youtu.be/t4kfZBI34bY"&gt;Using Poll Everywhere for Engagement and Assessment&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;By the end of this session, participants should be able to:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Describe the different levels of Bloom&amp;rsquo;s taxonomy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Construct / revise a poll question that helps students progress beyond recalling a selected course concept&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Unable to join us for this workshop? Engage with our on-demand resource: &lt;a href="https://ctl.columbia.edu/resources-and-technology/resources/poll-questions-stem/"&gt;Developing Poll Questions to Engage and Assess Student Thinking in Science and Engineering Courses&lt;/a&gt;. You can also schedule a &lt;a href="https://ctl.columbia.edu/faculty/offerings/consultations/"&gt;consultation&lt;/a&gt;, or find other workshops on our &lt;a href="https://ctl.columbia.edu/events/"&gt;CTL events calendar&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
